Bay 35th Street, west side, between Cropsey (right) and Warehouse (left) Aves. In the foreground is a lane that bears no name in the Atlases of Brooklyn from 1890-1929. However, the photographer, P.L. Sperr states it to be Centre Place.
April 27, 1935.
P.L. Sperr.
